## CI/CD — GitHub Actions con self-hosted runner

Los builds y tests corren en hardware propio, no en los minutos de GitHub.

### Configurar el runner

```
GitHub → repo → Settings → Actions → Runners → New self-hosted runner
```

Seguir los 3 comandos que da GitHub en la máquina local o en un Droplet dedicado.

### Workflow (esquema)

```yaml
on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: self-hosted
    steps:
      - php artisan test

  build:
    runs-on: self-hosted
    needs: test
    steps:
      - docker build streamer-php, streamer-queue, streamer-scheduler, streamer-nginx, streamer-socketio
      - docker push → DO Container Registry

  deploy:
    runs-on: self-hosted
    needs: build
    steps:
      - kubectl apply -f k8s/
      # o: kubectl set image deployment/php php=$REGISTRY/streamer-php:$TAG
```

El workflow usa `runs-on: self-hosted` — la única diferencia respecto a GitHub-hosted runners.

### Secrets requeridos en GitHub

| Secret | Valor |
|---|---|
| `DO_REGISTRY` | URL del container registry de DO |
| `DO_REGISTRY_TOKEN` | Token para push de imágenes |
| `KUBECONFIG` | kubeconfig del cluster DOKS |

